overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and an existing Statement of
  Work. The goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to implement
  any identified missing features. The agent performed an initial review,
  generating a detailed plan with prioritized action items. Subsequently, the
  agent proceeded to implement three key features: a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness with critical safety warnings, detection and tailored
  recommendations for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), and logic for
  identifying and providing guidance on Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. This
  involved modifying data types, validation rules, user interface components,
  and report generation logic to integrate these new functionalities
  seamlessly."
